summary: i know in the past ive mentioned that spoilers shouldn’t be posted until a week after it’s friday premiere. however since...
body:
i know in the past ive mentioned that spoilers shouldn’t be posted until a week after it’s friday premiere. however since endgame is not only the most anticipated mcu film thus far, but also this year it’s only fair to extend the ‘no spoiler’ period. two maybe even three weeks should be fair enough.

to each their own, but if you “must” for some reason or another have to post something related to an endgame spoiler please tag it. pure reaction posts with no context given about the movie are also fine.

thanks,

becca

title: The Mommy Quandary
body:
read it on the AO3 at http://bit.ly/2Un8pCz

by jay_girl88

“Fury and Coulson’s eyes were on her, but Toni couldn’t remove her gaze from where her boyfriend was already excitedly reminiscing with the man he knew as his old friend.

Was this karma for all the times that she’d hooked and booked with guys specifically chosen to piss Howard off? It had to be.”

~*~*~*~

When Howard Stark is somehow thrown into the future, Toni has to figure out a way to keep her longtime boyfriend from finding out just why she hated his old friend, keep her adopted not-son Peter away from the abusive older Stark, and find a way to send the man back without letting him glean too much about the future, all while watching Steve bro-bond with her dear old dad and reminding people that she was not remotely mother material so everyone just stop encouraging Peter to call her Mommy, damn it!

Piece of cake.

summary: See, I think the reason a large ensemble superhero movie doesn’t really work is that the writers and directors always focus on...
body:
See, I think the reason a large ensemble superhero movie doesn’t really work is that the writers and directors always focus on one character more than the others. That is why I feel like Infinity War was a disappointment. T’challa doesn’t come into the movie until the very end and he was OOC because the Russos dislike him. The Guardians were fine but I’m still angry that Gamora had to die for the plot. I’m really sick of female characters having to die for dudes. And there is all this focus on Tony which is also annoying because he’s had three solo movies, two Avengers film and a Captain America film in which he played a huge role.

People say the MCU works and I feel like it only does when the movies themselves are contained.
